# An empty Cornell Box with cyan and orange walls in OBJ format.
# Note that the real box is not a perfect cube, so
# the faces are imperfect in this data set.
#
# Created by Guedis Cardenas and Morgan McGuire at Williams College, 2011
# Released into the Public Domain.
#
# http://graphics.cs.williams.edu/data
# http://www.graphics.cornell.edu/online/box/data.html
#

mtllib CornellBox-Empty-CO.mtl

# Object floor
v  -1.01  0.00   0.99
v   1.00  0.00   0.99
v   1.00  0.00  -1.04
v  -0.99  0.00  -1.04
vn  0.0 1.0 0.0

g floor
usemtl floor
f 4//1 3//1 2//1 1//1

# Object ceiling 
v  -1.02  1.99   0.99  
v  -1.02  1.99  -1.04
v   1.00  1.99  -1.04
v   1.00  1.99   0.99
vn  0.0 -1.0 0.0

g ceiling
usemtl ceiling
f 4//2 3//2 2//2 1//2

# Object backwall  
v  -0.99  0.00  -1.04 
v   1.00  0.00  -1.04
v   1.00  1.99  -1.04
v  -1.02  1.99  -1.04
vn  0.0 0.0 -1.0

g backWall
usemtl backWall
f 4//3 3//3 2//3 1//3

## Object rightwall 
v	1.00  0.00  -1.04   
v	1.00  0.00   0.99
v	1.00  1.99   0.99
v	1.00  1.99  -1.04
vn  1.0 0.0 0.0

g rightWall
usemtl rightWall
f 4//4 3//4 2//4 1//4

## Object leftWall   
v  -1.01  0.00   0.99
v  -0.99  0.00  -1.04
v  -1.02  1.99  -1.04
v  -1.02  1.99   0.99
vn  -1.0 0.0 0.0

g leftWall
usemtl leftWall
f 4//5 3//5 2//5 1//5

## Object light 
v	-0.24  1.98   0.16
v	-0.24  1.98  -0.22
v	 0.23  1.98  -0.22
v	 0.23  1.98   0.16
vn  0.0 -1.0 0.0

g light
usemtl light
f 4//6 3//6 2//6 1//6